def: A short line attached to a trawl. See Trawl, n.
The state or quality of being infrangible; infrangibility.

An imitation of any veined and ornamental stone, as marble,formed by a substratum of finely ground gypsum mixed with glue, thesurface of which, while soft, is variegated with splinters of marble,spar, granite, etc., and subsequently colored and polished.
A small copper coin, with a mixture of silver, formerly currentin some parts of Germany and Switzerland. It was worth about fourcents.
A thickened glandular portion of the body of the adultearthworm, consisting of several united segments modified forreproductive purposes.
To represent by an emblem; to emblematize. [R.]
Having a suburb or suburbs on its outer part.
